d995b","position":"1784784416210295001-74185e3a-cc68-4e82-b11e-3e29affdd2b2"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"c5fcb16882e401b2c9ee714a206a2a05a9b96c345565a0272f0ff249183cbb3b","event_uuid":"ecf16633-a792-4296-b00f-e6f95d6020bb","position":{"commit_sha":"3f08e60ed0d80064a46d2502d41e1a42be775080","position":"1784784597096752001-ecf16633-a792-4296-b00f-e6f95d6020bb"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"85ef1f001a7e11c686ef53dab1c11d825d07e7dbdc9c5eab8160c640ba12e0ed","event_uuid":"9245b3b8-7917-4726-a658-e38810872cbb","position":{"commit_sha":"3f08e60ed0d80064a46d2502d41e1a42be775080","position":"1784784597404710001-9245b3b8-7917-4726-a658-e38810872cbb"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-218_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"c4bc0a36-ab8e-4f75-b7cc-ef7f0aae74e2","comments":[],"created_at":1784781360855546001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"Make the commit-trailer format + all CLI-served guides resolve for repo-less clients\n\n## Context / Problem\n\nClients using the `rebar` CLI **without a rebar checkout** hit dead ends in CLI-served prose.\nToday's commit `c2bfbe217` packaged the two author guides into `src/rebar/_guides/` so\n`rebar explain plan|review` serves them from any install — but it left the guides' **internal\ncross-references** as consumer-relative paths (`review-policy.md`, `review-kernel.md`,\n`../CONTRIBUTING.md`, `plan-review-gate.md`, `plan-review-criteria-guide.md`,\n`docs/commit-ticket-trailer.md`, `AGENTS.md`), which dangle for a consumer with no such tree —\nthe same class of dead-consumer-link bug that `62933ff62` fixed for plan-review deep-links\n(\"client report §5\"). Separately, the required `rebar-ticket: <id>` commit-trailer format\n(`EXPECTED_FORMAT` in `verify_commit.py`) has **no** CLI-discoverable home at all: only\n`rebar verify-commit-ticket --help` prints it, and nothing points there. The remediation was\nnot comprehensive.\n\n## Approach\n\nTwo moves, both grounded in conventions already in this repo:\n\n1. **Give the trailer a first-class CLI home.** Add a third packaged author guide,\n   `src/rebar/_guides/commit-ticket-trailer.md`, registered as the `commit-trailer` topic in\n   `AUTHOR_GUIDES` (`registry.py`) — served offline by `rebar explain commit-trailer` and the\n   MCP `explain_guide` tool, exactly like `plan`/`review`. It quotes `EXPECTED_FORMAT` verbatim\n   (drift-pinned by test) plus how-to-self-check prose (`rebar verify-commit-ticket`).\n\n2. **Repoint every dangling reference in the packaged guides** so it resolves for a repo-less\n   consumer, using the established two-way convention: sibling packaged guides →\n   `rebar explain <topic>`; repo-only docs → the canonical hosted base\n   `https://github.com/navapbc/rebar/blob/main/…` (the same base `62933ff62`'s\n   `_DEFAULT_DOCS_URL` and pyproject `[project.urls] Documentation` already use).\n\nThen lock it with a guard test asserting no packaged `_guides/*.md` link target is a\nconsumer-relative path (only `https://`, intra-doc `#anchor`, or `rebar explain` are allowed) —\nso the remediation stays comprehensive. Rejected: a bespoke `rebar trailer-format` subcommand\n(`explain` is already the on-ramp for `plan`/`review`; a third topic needs no new wiring);\nrejected shipping the whole `docs/` tree in the wheel (heavy; hosted URLs already resolve).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/_guides/commit-ticket-trailer.md` — NEW packaged guide; quotes `EXPECTED_FORMAT`\n  verbatim + `rebar verify-commit-ticket` self-check prose; links only via `https://`/`rebar explain`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/registry.py` — add `\"commit-trailer\"` → the new file in `AUTHOR_GUIDES`.\n- `src/rebar/_mcp_reads.py` — the MCP `explain_criterion` tool docstring hardcodes the guide\n  list (`plan`/`review`); add `commit-trailer` so MCP clients discover it (the tool dispatch at\n  L63 already reads `AUTHOR_GUIDES` dynamically — only the human-facing docstring lags).\n- `src/rebar/_guides/passing-code-review.md` — repoint L5 review-policy/review-kernel + L6/L39\n  CONTRIBUTING to hosted URLs; L8 sibling → `rebar explain plan`; L35 trailer →\n  `rebar explain commit-trailer` + `rebar verify-commit-ticket --help`.\n- `src/rebar/_guides/writing-a-passing-plan.md` — repoint L6 criteria-guide + L7\n  plan-review-gate to hosted URLs; L8 sibling → `rebar explain review`.\n- `tests/unit/test_verify_commit_ticket.py` — drift assertion (packaged guide quotes\n  `EXPECTED_FORMAT`).\n- `tests/unit/test_plan_review_explain.py` — `rebar explain commit-trailer` returns the format;\n  unknown-guide error lists it; LINK-RESOLUTION guard test (below); a guard asserting every\n  `AUTHOR_GUIDES` key is named in the MCP `explain_criterion` docstring (so the MCP guide list\n  can't silently drift from the registry again).\n- `tests/unit/test_engine_dir.py` — make the existing `test_wheel_ships_author_guides` iterate\n  `AUTHOR_GUIDES` (not a hardcoded pair) so the new guide — and any future one — is packaging-\n  guarded automatically.\n- `AGENTS.md` — one-line pointer to `rebar explain commit-trailer` in the trailer bullet.\n- `docs/commit-ticket-trailer.md` — note the CLI discovery paths.\n\n## Testing\n\n- Happy: `registry.explain_guide(\"commit-trailer\")` and CLI `rebar explain commit-trailer` both\n  return text containing `EXPECTED_FORMAT` (exit 0).\n- Edge: unknown guide name raises `ExplainError(\"unknown-id\", …)` whose message now lists\n  `commit-trailer`.\n- Drift: the packaged guide contains `EXPECTED_FORMAT` verbatim.\n- Link-resolution guard (the core regression-proofing): a single test enumerates ALL\n  in-command help prose a repo-less client can see — every registered `AUTHOR_GUIDES` guide\n  body AND every `explain_criterion(<id>)` rendering — extracts every markdown link `](target)`,\n  and asserts each target RESOLVES for a non-rebar client. The one canonical allow-list, used\n  everywhere: a target is OK iff it starts with `https://`, `http://`, `#` (intra-doc anchor),\n  or `mailto:`. Any consumer-relative path (`](*.md)`, `](docs/…)`, `](../…)`) FAILS. A second\n  axis scans the packaged guide bodies (only) for bare parenthetical/inline repo paths\n  (`docs/…`, `../…`) not part of a hosted `…/blob/main/…` URL — catching non-hyperlink dead\n  references the `](…)` regex misses. It also validates every `rebar explain <topic>` mentioned\n  in that prose names a real registered guide/criterion, so the reachable-pointer claim can't\n  rot. Driven by the registries (not a hardcoded file list) so new guides/criteria are covered\n  automatically.\n- Full `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `rebar explain commit-trailer` exits 0 and prints the canonical trailer format (run it;\n      CLI unit test asserts `EXPECTED_FORMAT` in stdout).\n- [ ] `commit-trailer` is listed among known guides in `rebar explain` help and the\n      `unknown-id` error (unit test).\n- [ ] The packaged `commit-ticket-trailer.md` quotes `EXPECTED_FORMAT` verbatim (drift test).\n- [ ] The link-resolution guard passes: across every `AUTHOR_GUIDES` guide body and every\n      `explain_criterion(<id>)` rendering, no markdown link target is consumer-relative (allowed\n      set is exactly `https://`/`http://`/`#anchor`/`mailto:`), no packaged guide has a bare\n      `docs/…`/`../…` path, and every `rebar explain <topic>` cited names a real registered\n      guide/criterion (test passes; verified by grep too).\n- [ ] `rebar explain review` and `rebar explain plan` no longer reference repo-relative files;\n      sibling guides read as `rebar explain <topic>`, repo docs as `https://github.com/navapbc/…`\n      — confirmed by the link-resolution guard passing (a manual read may spot-check readability).\n- [ ] `docs/commit-ticket-trailer.md` names `rebar explain commit-trailer` and\n      `rebar verify-commit-ticket` as CLI discovery paths (grep the file).\n- [ ] The MCP `explain_criterion` tool docstring names `commit-trailer`, and a guard test\n      asserts every `AUTHOR_GUIDES` key appears in that docstring (test passes).\n- [ ] AGENTS.md's trailer bullet names `rebar explain commit-trailer` (grep).\n- [ ] `make lint`, `make typecheck`, `make test` all pass (run them).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_guides/commit-ticket-trailer.md","reason":"new packaged guide served by rebar explain commit-trailer"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/registry.py","reason":"register commit-trailer topic in AUTHOR_GUIDES"},{"path":"src/rebar/_mcp_reads.py","reason":"update MCP explain_criterion docstring to include commit-trailer"},{"path":"src/rebar/_guides/passing-code-review.md","reason":"repoint dangling refs to rebar explain / hosted URLs"},{"path":"src/rebar/_guides/writing-a-passing-plan.md","reason":"repoint dangling refs to rebar explain / hosted URLs"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_verify_commit_ticket.py","reason":"drift assertion for packaged guide"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_plan_review_explain.py","reason":"explain commit-trailer + link-resolution guard + mcp-docstring guard"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_engine_dir.py","reason":"wheel-ships-guides test iterates AUTHOR_GUIDES"},{"path":"AGENTS.md","reason":"one-line pointer to rebar explain commit-trailer"},{"path":"docs/commit-ticket-trailer.md","reason":"note CLI discovery paths"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"ecf16633-a792-4296-b00f-e6f95d6020bb","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"0447-9a5c-d74c-4b0a","ticket_type":"task","title":"Make commit-trailer format + CLI-served guides resolve for repo-less clients","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["5a31d94b-84cb-49de-a063-b5852f5ea4cc","befe670b-0309-4425-b09f-df93988a5bee","2f23ad42-86d8-40ac-aa32-884439e8f070","25ed2982-7086-4625-8f41-113d6b7293b4","d3f8fb8d-f14a-4299-93f7-eba023b8ba81","cc1d2c3b-409c-4593-bc34-448162fdacd4","74185e3a-cc68-4e82-b11e-3e29affdd2b2","ecf16633-a792-4296-b00f-e6f95d6020bb","9245b3b8-7917-4726-a658-e38810872cbb"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784784597404710002,"uuid":"d0474402-803e-49bd-9864-0fe2f8e4b979"}